pean Championship]] \u2014 '''3rd place'''\n*:[[Bianka Bu\u0161a]], [[Bojana \u017divkovi\u0107]], [[Mina Popovi\u0107]], [[Tijana Male\u0161evi\u0107]], [[Brankica Mihajlovi\u0107]], [[Maja Ognjenovi\u0107]], [[Stefana Veljkovi\u0107]], [[Jelena Nikoli\u0107]], [[Ana Bjelica]], [[Jovana Stevanovi\u0107]], [[Milena Ra\u0161i\u0107]], [[Silvija Popovi\u0107]], [[Suzana \u0106ebi\u0107]], [[Tijana Bo\u0161kovi\u0107]]. Head Coach: [[Zoran Terzi\u0107]].\n* [[Volleyball at the 2016 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|2016 Olympics]] \u2014 '''2nd place'''\n*:[[Bianka Bu\u0161a]], [[Jovana Brako\u010devi\u0107]], [[Bojana \u017divkovi\u0107]], [[Tijana Male\u0161evi\u0107]], [[Brankica Mihajlovi\u0107]], [[Maja Ognjenovi\u0107]], [[Stefana Veljkovi\u0107]], [[Jelena Nikoli\u0107]], [[Jovana Stevanovi\u0107]], [[Milena Ra\u0161i\u0107]], [[Silvija Popovi\u0107]], [[Tijana Bo\u0161kovi\u0107]]. Head Coach: [[Zoran Terzi\u0107]].\n* [[2017 Women's European Volleyball Championship|2017 European Championship]] \u2014 '''1st place'''\n*:[[Bianka Bu\u0161a]], [[Ana Bjelica]], [[Bojana \u017divkovi\u0107]], [[Tijana Male\u0161evi\u0107]], [[Brankica Mihajlovi\u0107]], [[Stefana Veljkovi\u0107]], [[Jovana Stevanovi\u0107]], [[Milena Ra\u0161i\u0107]], [[Tijana Bo\u0161kovi\u0107]], [[Sla\u0111ana Mirkovi\u0107]], [[Jelena Blagojevi\u0107]], [[Bojana Milenkovi\u0107]], [[Silvija Popovi\u0107]], [[Teodora Pu\u0161i\u0107]]. Head Coach: [[Zoran Terzi\u0107]].\n\n===Coaches===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!align=\"left\" style=\"width: 10em\"| Name\n!align=\"left\" style=\"width: 4em\"|From\n!align=\"left\" style=\"width: 4em\"|Until\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SRB}} [[Darko Zako\u010d]]\n|align=\"center\"|1996\n|align=\"center\"|2001\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SRB}} [[Zoran Terzi\u0107]]\n|align=\"center\"|2002\n|align=\"center\"|''present''\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Yugoslavia women's national volleyball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{commons category|Serbi